    <!-- ═══ SECTION 2: FLOWS ═══ -->
    <section id="flows" class="docs-section">
      <h2 class="section-anchor">Flows</h2>
      <p>The complete journey from "I want to watch something" to "it's streaming on my TV."</p>

      <h3 id="main-flow">Request → Search → Download → Stream</h3>
      <div class="mermaid-wrap"><pre class="mermaid">
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Seerr as Jellyseerr
    participant Arr as Arr App
    participant Prowlarr
    participant VPN as Gluetun VPN
    participant DL as Download Client
    participant Library
    participant Jellyfin
    User->>Seerr: "I want The Matrix"
    Seerr->>Arr: Add to wanted list
    Arr->>Prowlarr: Search all indexers
    Prowlarr-->>Arr: Results from 12 indexers
    Arr->>Arr: Score with Custom Formats
    alt Torrent
        Arr->>DL: Send to Transmission
        DL->>VPN: Download through tunnel
        DL-->>Arr: Complete
        Arr->>Library: HARDLINK
    else Usenet
        Arr->>DL: Send to SABnzbd
        DL->>VPN: Download through tunnel
        DL-->>Arr: Complete
        Arr->>Library: MOVE
    end
    Library-->>Jellyfin: New file detected
    Jellyfin-->>User: Ready to watch
      </pre></div>

      <h3 id="vpn-killswitch">VPN Kill Switch</h3>
      <div class="mermaid-wrap"><pre class="mermaid">
sequenceDiagram
    participant DL as Download Client
    participant FW as Firewall iptables
    participant VPN as VPN Tunnel
    participant Internet
    Note over VPN: Tunnel drops
    DL->>FW: Try to download
    FW--xDL: BLOCKED kill switch
    Note over DL: Zero traffic leaks
    FW->>VPN: Re-establish tunnel
    VPN->>Internet: Connected
    DL->>FW: Try again
    FW->>VPN: Route through tunnel
    VPN->>Internet: Download resumes
      </pre></div>
      <div class="callout">The kill switch uses iptables with a default DROP policy. Only VPN tunnel traffic, Docker-internal communication, and WireGuard handshake packets are allowed. IPv6 fully blocked.</div>

      <h3 id="search-vs-download">Search vs Download Traffic</h3>
      <div class="mermaid-wrap"><pre class="mermaid">
graph LR
    subgraph SEARCH["Search Traffic — Direct, no VPN"]
        ARR["Arr Apps"] -->|"HTTPS"| IDX["Indexer Sites"]
        PW["Prowlarr"] -->|"via FlareSolverr"| CF["CF-Protected Sites"]
    end
    subgraph DOWNLOAD["Download Traffic — VPN encrypted"]
        TX["Transmission"] -->|"WireGuard"| TRK["Torrent Trackers"]
        SB["SABnzbd"] -->|"WireGuard"| USN["Usenet Servers"]
    end
    style SEARCH fill:#89b4fa,color:#1e1e2e
    style DOWNLOAD fill:#f38ba8,color:#1e1e2e
      </pre></div>

      <h3 id="indexer-architecture">Indexer Architecture</h3>
      <div class="mermaid-wrap"><pre class="mermaid">
graph TD
    PW["Prowlarr — Central Manager"]
    subgraph TORRENT["8 Torrent Indexers"]
        T1["1337x"] & T2["EZTV"] & T3["Knaben"] & T4["LimeTorrents"]
        T5["Nyaa.si"] & T6["SkidrowRepack"] & T7["The Pirate Bay"] & T8["YTS"]
    end
    subgraph USENET["4 Usenet Indexers"]
        U1["NZBFinder"] & U2["NZBgeek"] & U3["NzbPlanet"] & U4["Usenet-Crawler"]
    end
    PW -->|"with FlareSolverr"| TORRENT
    PW -->|"API key auth"| USENET
    PW ==>|"fullSync every 6h"| RD["Radarr"] & SN["Sonarr"] & LD["Lidarr"]
      </pre></div>

