      </pre></div>

      <h3 id="usenet-tiers">Usenet Server Tiers</h3>
      <div class="mermaid-wrap"><pre class="mermaid">
graph TD
    SB["SABnzbd"] -->|"Priority 0 — 100 conn"| P0["Primary Backbone"]
    SB -->|"Priority 1 — 8 conn"| P1["Fill Server"]
    SB -->|"Priority 2 — 40 conn"| P2["Backup Servers"]
    P0 -->|"missing"| P1 -->|"still missing"| P2
      </pre></div>

      <h3 id="torrent-vs-usenet">Torrent vs Usenet</h3>
      <div class="table-wrap"><table>
        <thead><tr><th>Feature</th><th>Torrent</th><th>Usenet</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td>Protocol</td><td>Peer-to-peer</td><td>Client-server</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Cost</td><td>Free</td><td>Paid subscription</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Speed</td><td>Varies by seeders</td><td>Saturates bandwidth</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Seeding</td><td>Must seed back (hardlinks!)</td><td>No obligation</td></tr>
          <tr><td>Weakness</td><td>Slow for old/rare</td><td>DMCA takedowns</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table></div>

      <h3 id="hardlink-flow">The Hardlink Flow</h3>
      <div class="mermaid-wrap"><pre class="mermaid">
sequenceDiagram
    participant TX as Transmission
    participant FS as Filesystem
    participant RD as Radarr
    participant JF as Jellyfin
    TX->>FS: Download complete, inode #3899
    TX->>TX: Continue seeding
    RD->>FS: Hardlink to /media/movies/
    Note over FS: Two filenames, one set of data blocks
    JF->>FS: Stream from library path
    Note over TX: Eventually stop seeding
    TX->>FS: Delete download path
    Note over FS: inode still has 1 link — data persists
      </pre></div>
      <div class="callout callout-warn"><strong>Common mistake:</strong> Two separate volume mounts = cross-device hardlink fails = files get COPIED = disk doubles. Always use a single mount <code>-v /data:/data</code>.</div>

      <h3 id="dns">DNS Architecture</h3>
      <div class="mermaid-wrap"><pre class="mermaid">
graph TD
    subgraph VPN_DNS["Inside VPN"]
        TX["Transmission"] & SB["SABnzbd"] --> GDNS["Gluetun DNS"]
        GDNS -->|"Through tunnel"| CF["Cloudflare DNS"]
    end
    subgraph BRIDGE["Bridge Network"]
        APPS["Arr Apps"] -->|"Hardcoded public DNS"| PUBLIC["Public DNS"]
    end
    subgraph HOST["Host Network"]
        JF["Jellyfin"] --> SYS["System DNS"]
    end
    style VPN_DNS fill:#f38ba8,color:#1e1e2e
      </pre></div>

      <h3 id="game-pipeline">Game Pipeline</h3>
      <div class="mermaid-wrap"><pre class="mermaid">
sequenceDiagram
    participant QA as QuestArr
    participant DL as Download Client
    participant CRON as game-import.sh
    participant LIB as Game Library
    QA->>DL: User picks a game
    DL->>DL: Downloads through VPN
    loop Every 15 minutes
        CRON->>DL: Download finished?
        DL-->>CRON: Yes
        CRON->>CRON: Safety checks
        alt Torrent
            CRON->>LIB: Hardlink
        else Usenet
            CRON->>LIB: Move
        end
    end
      </pre></div>

      <h3 id="book-sorting">Book Sorting</h3>
      <div class="mermaid-wrap"><pre class="mermaid">
graph TD
    DL["Download completes"] -->|"Every 10 min"| PP["PostProcessor"]
    PP --> DETECT{"File type?"}
    DETECT -->|"epub/pdf/mobi"| EBOOKS["/media/books/ — Kavita"]
    DETECT -->|"mp3/m4b/m4a"| AUDIO["/media/audiobooks/ — Audiobookshelf"]
      </pre></div>

      <h3 id="subtitle-flow">Subtitle Flow</h3>
      <div class="mermaid-wrap"><pre class="mermaid">
graph TD
    TRIGGER["New media imported"] & SCHEDULE["Wanted scan every 6h"]
    TRIGGER & SCHEDULE --> BZ["Bazarr"]
    BZ --> PROV["Query subtitle providers"]
    PROV --> SCORE["Score against media metadata"]
    SCORE --> THRESH{"Above threshold?"}
    THRESH -->|"Yes"| DL["Download .srt"]
    THRESH -->|"No"| SKIP["Skip"]
    DL --> PLACE["Place alongside media file"]
    PLACE --> JF["Jellyfin auto-detects"]
      </pre></div>
    </section>

    <!-- ═══ SECTION 3: QUALITY ═══ -->
    <section id="quality" class="docs-section">
      <h2 class="section-anchor">Quality &amp; Selection</h2>
      <p>How the stack decides which release to download when multiple options exist.</p>

      <h3 id="decision-engine">The Decision Engine</h3>
      <div class="mermaid-wrap"><pre class="mermaid">
graph TD
    RELEASE["Incoming Release"] --> Q{"Quality allowed?"}
    Q -->|"No"| R1["REJECTED"]
    Q -->|"Yes"| CF["Score Custom Formats"]
    CF --> BAD{"Any -10000 CF?"}
    BAD -->|"Yes"| R2["REJECTED"]
    BAD -->|"No"| MIN{"Score >= minimum?"}
    MIN -->|"No"| R3["REJECTED"]
    MIN -->|"Yes"| RANK["ACCEPTED — ranked by score"]
    RANK --> BEST["Highest score grabbed"]
    BEST --> UP{"Better than existing?"}
    UP -->|"Yes"| UPGRADE["UPGRADE"]
    UP -->|"No"| SKIP["SKIP"]
    style R1 fill:#f38ba8,color:#1e1e2e
    style R2 fill:#f38ba8,color:#1e1e2e
    style R3 fill:#f38ba8,color:#1e1e2e
    style UPGRADE fill:#a6e3a1,color:#1e1e2e
      </pre></div>

      <h3 id="custom-formats">Custom Format Scoring</h3>
      <h4>Radarr — Movies (48 Custom Formats)</h4>
      <div class="mermaid-wrap"><pre class="mermaid">
graph LR
    subgraph POSITIVE["Positive Scores"]
        direction TB
